Creativity. Process of creativity. Development of children's' drawings.  Arts therapies in the contexts of education. Art therapies as theoretical background for application of creative work in socialpedagogy.  Art therapies as background of the praxis of creative group work (art, music, drama, dance/movement) working with problematic children and adolescents.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to create presuppositions for socialpedagogical practical creative work (art, music, drama, and dance/movement) with children and adolescents.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completing the course a student will be able to: Have knowledge's about theoretical approaches to applying creative work (art, music, drama, movement/dance) in the area of socialpedagogogy; demonstrates presuppositions for applying and practicing creative group work (art, music, drama, movement/dance) working with pupils who have social problems.
